ShortName: Loss functions & optimization
Topic: calculus
Concepts: A function as input→output and its graph as a curve (`function`, `curve()`); a loss/objective/cost function measuring "how wrong," with a parameter as the knob; slope zero at a valley bottom and the recipe "differentiate, set to zero, solve" ($\arg\min$ vs the minimum); applying the chain rule and sum rule to differentiate a squared-error loss; letting a computer search downhill when algebra can't solve it (`optimize()`, `optim()`)
BuildsOn: [derivative-as-slope](derivative-as-slope/lesson.qmd), [differentiation-rules](differentiation-rules/lesson.qmd), [vectors-and-summation](vectors-and-summation/lesson.qmd), [mean-variance-covariance](mean-variance-covariance/lesson.qmd)
UsedBy: [simple-linear-regression](../courses/simple-linear-regression/syllabus.md)
